text: Yongkang (永康) may refer to: * Yongkang District, Tainan, Taiwan ==Locations in Mainland China== * Yongkang, Zhejiang, a city in Zhejiang * Yongkang Subdistrict, a subdistrict in Taonan, Jilin * Yongkang, Anhui, a town in Dingyuan County, Anhui * Yongkang, Ningxia, a town in Zhongwei, Ningxia * Yongkang, Yunnan, a town in Yongde County, Yunnan ==Historical eras== *Yongkang (167), an era name used by Emperor Xuan of Han *Yongkang (300–301), an era name used by Emperor Hui of Jin *Yongkang (396–398), an era name used by Murong Bao, emperor of Later Yan *Yongkang (412–419), an era name used by Qifu Chipan, ruler of Western Qin *Yongkang (464–484), an era name used by Yujiulü Yucheng, khan of Rouran
title: Yongkang
